<paragraph blockId="3.[125,1173,888,1039]" lastBlockId="4.[138,1185,944,1682]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="447" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
Since no copy of 
<bibRefCitation author="Sabussow HP" box="[331,552,888,912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref9011" refString="Sabussow HP. 1900. Beobachtungen uber die Turbellarien der Inseln von Solowetzk. Trudy Obshchestva Estestvoispytatelei pri Imperatorskom Kazanskom Universitete 34: 1 - 208, pls I - III (in Russian, with German summary)." type="journal article" year="1900">Sabussow’s (1900)</bibRefCitation>
paper was available at the time, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sluys R" box="[938,1089,888,912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" refId="ref9110" refString="Sluys R. 1989. A Monograph of the Marine Triclads. Rotterdam and Brookfield: A. A. Balkema. XII + 463 p." type="book" year="1989">Sluys (1989)</bibRefCitation>
had to rely on the summaries provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilhelmi J" box="[527,720,920,944]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" refId="ref9500" refString="Wilhelmi J. 1909. Tricladen, Fauna und Flora des Golfes von Neapel. 32, Berlin: R. Friedlander und Sohn. xii + 405 p, 16 pls." type="book" year="1909">Wilhelmi (1909)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bohmig L" box="[775,955,920,944]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" pagination="344 - 504" refId="ref8748" refString="Bohmig L. 1906. Tricladenstudien I: Tricladida Maricola. Zeitschrift fur Wissenschaftliche Zoologie 81: 344 - 504." type="journal article" year="1906">Böhmig (1906)</bibRefCitation>
, workers who both pointed to the incomplete and inadequate original description of the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Sabussow, 1900" authorityName="Sabussow" authorityYear="1900" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="solowetzkianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Procerodes solowetzkianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sabussow HP" box="[294,482,983,1007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref9011" refString="Sabussow HP. 1900. Beobachtungen uber die Turbellarien der Inseln von Solowetzk. Trudy Obshchestva Estestvoispytatelei pri Imperatorskom Kazanskom Universitete 34: 1 - 208, pls I - III (in Russian, with German summary)." type="journal article" year="1900">Sabussow, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Solovetskiye Islands in the White Sea. When R.S. obtained a personal copy of Sabussow’s paper, no new light was thrown on the enigmatic status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sabussow" authorityYear="1900" box="[251,449,944,968]" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="solowetzkianus">
<emphasis box="[251,449,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">P. solowetzkianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, albeit that thus there was direct access to the drawing of a sagittal section of the copulatory apparatus (
<figureCitation box="[657,758,977,1001]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="3.[125,185,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[346,950,1079,1600]" captionTargetId="figure-220@3.[344,953,1076,1601]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 1. Foviella affinis, sagittal section through copulatory apparatus (from Sabussow 1900: pl. III, figure 34; labels adapted according to current terminology)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221455/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Figure 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221455" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5221455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" startId="3.[125,185,1637,1656]" targetBox="[346,950,1079,1600]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[125,1172,1637,1682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
Figure 1. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oersted" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[222,352,1637,1656]" family="Uteriporidae" genus="Foviella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[222,352,1637,1656]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Foviella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sagittal section through copulatory apparatus (from 
<bibRefCitation author="Sabussow HP" box="[854,1003,1637,1656]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref9011" refString="Sabussow HP. 1900. Beobachtungen uber die Turbellarien der Inseln von Solowetzk. Trudy Obshchestva Estestvoispytatelei pri Imperatorskom Kazanskom Universitete 34: 1 - 208, pls I - III (in Russian, with German summary)." type="journal article" year="1900">Sabussow 1900</bibRefCitation>
: pl. III, figure 34; labels adapted according to current terminology).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221457" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5221457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" startId="4.[138,207,835,854]" targetBox="[245,1077,133,797]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[138,1185,835,881]" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">
Figures 2, 3. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oersted" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[266,394,835,854]" family="Uteriporidae" genus="Foviella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[266,394,835,854]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Foviella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (2) V.Pl. 948.3, sagittal section of the copulatory apparatus. (3) V.Pl. 948.3, sagittal section through eye cup with lens.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[138,1185,944,1682]" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">
Russian workers continued to report 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sabussow" authorityYear="1900" box="[603,797,1009,1033]" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="solowetzkianus">
<emphasis box="[603,797,1009,1033]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">P. solowetzkianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the White Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Timoshkin OA" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" refId="ref9429" refString="Timoshkin OA. 1979. Turbellarians of the Chupa Bay, White Sea. Unpublished student report, University of Kazan, Faculty of Benthic Biology, 26 p. (in Russian)." type="book" year="1979">Timoshkin 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poljakova AA" box="[212,392,1042,1066]" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" refId="ref8966" refString="Poljakova AA. 1991. Tricladida maricola in the Seas of the USSR / White Sea, Black Sea and Far Eastern Sea. Unpublished student report, University of Kazan, Chair of Invertebrate Zoology, 57 p. (in Russian)." type="book" year="1991">Poljakova 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and when finally new material became available it was immediately clear how Sabussow’s account should be correctly interpreted. It turned out that a good deal of misunderstanding had been caused by the fact that Sabussow described as a small, ball-shaped ‘Uterus’ (i.e. copulatory bursa) a structure that actually is the very distal end of the female genital duct, in point of fact the precise point where the oviducts communicate with the genital duct. A copulatory bursa, as present in many maricolans, is actually missing in these animals from the White Sea. Examination of histological sections unequivocally revealed that the specimens are representatives of the species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Oersted, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Oersted" baseAuthorityYear="1843" family="Uteriporidae" genus="Foviella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[897,1062,1269,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Foviella affinis</emphasis>
(Oersted, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
. This species is further characterized by: (1) a female genital duct receiving the secretion of penial glands; (2) a well-muscularized penial papilla with a distinct caudally directed bend or with the tip of the papilla curved towards the dorsal body surface; (3) vasa deferentia that expand within the penis bulb to form intrabulbar spermiducal vesicles before uniting to form the ejaculatory duct; and (4) a large lens in each eye cup. All of these features occur in our presumed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sabussow" authorityYear="1900" box="[558,761,1463,1487]" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="solowetzkianus">
<emphasis box="[558,761,1463,1487]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">P. solowetzkianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
animals, a finding that we here substantiate by providing a photograph of a sagittal section of the copulatory apparatus (
<figureCitation box="[146,249,1528,1552]" captionStart="Figures 2, 3" captionStartId="4.[138,207,835,854]" captionTargetBox="[245,1077,133,797]" captionTargetId="figure-315@4.[245,1077,133,799]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 2, 3. Foviella affinis. (2) V.Pl. 948.3, sagittal section of the copulatory apparatus. (3) V.Pl. 948.3, sagittal section through eye cup with lens." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Figure 2</figureCitation>
) and of an eye cup with a lens (
<figureCitation box="[629,733,1528,1552]" captionStart="Figures 2, 3" captionStartId="4.[138,207,835,854]" captionTargetBox="[245,1077,133,797]" captionTargetId="figure-315@4.[245,1077,133,799]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 2, 3. Foviella affinis. (2) V.Pl. 948.3, sagittal section of the copulatory apparatus. (3) V.Pl. 948.3, sagittal section through eye cup with lens." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Figure 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[138,1185,944,1682]" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">
<bibRefCitation author="Sabussow HP" box="[165,384,1561,1585]" pageId="4" pageNumber="447" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref9011" refString="Sabussow HP. 1900. Beobachtungen uber die Turbellarien der Inseln von Solowetzk. Trudy Obshchestva Estestvoispytatelei pri Imperatorskom Kazanskom Universitete 34: 1 - 208, pls I - III (in Russian, with German summary)." type="journal article" year="1900">Sabussow’s (1900)</bibRefCitation>
description now turns out to be in close agreement with our findings based on examination of new material, since he depicted the curved nature of the penial papilla (his figures 32–34), the female genital duct receiving the secretion of shell glands (his figure 34) and the intrabulbar spermiducal vesicles (his figure 33).
</paragraph>
